<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Currently, the Zend_Http_Response code only supports HTTP responses that use CRLF as linebreaks.
While the RFC and standards all state that CRLF should be used - some servers break lines with just LF (and possibly just CR ?). Pages from these servers work well in Firefox and other browsers - but completely break with the Zend_Http_Client.</p>

<p>Support for servers that end lines with "\n" is highly recommended.</p>

